	<!-- About -->
	<div class="page" id="about_page">
		<div class="header">
			<div class="heading">About The Indus Dispatch</div>
			<div class="subheading">...and this website.</div>
		</div>

		<p>
			Welcome to the homepage of that most reputed publication, known to most as "The Indus Dispatch",
			this being primarily an archive of all editions of The Indus Dispatch since August of 2020.
		</p>

		<p>
			With what resources we're given, we endeavour to provide a somewhat entertaining read to our
			various patrons, who exceed the tens in number. Through academic pressures, and sub-zero pay, 
			we struggle on, in pursuit of that paradigm of pseudo-academic literary perfection. Just how far
			can one stray from academics before ceasing to be a school newsletter, in the strictest sense?
			Every day, we explore this question. At least, we think. We don't really know exactly what we do.
		</p>

		<p class="italic small"><i>
			All editions contained in these archives were produced under the management of Aarush Kumbhakern (Compiler/Primary Editor: 
